cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.CV 

The paper discusses the impact of non-idealities on resistive crossbars, which are a type of hardware fabric used for deep neural networks. This topic falls under the category of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET) and Architecture (cs.AR) as it deals with the design and implementation of hardware for DNNs. Additionally, the paper proposes a simulation framework for evaluating and re-training DNNs, which falls under the categories of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the experiments conducted in the paper evaluate large-scale DNNs developed for the ImageNet Challenge, which falls under the category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
